Adelani Adepegba, Abuja The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission has grilled a former governor of Zamfara State, Abdulaziz Yari over alleged illegal financial dealings. Yari was interrogated by EFCC operatives in Lagos on Wednesday, it was learnt. READ ALSO: Osinbajo should leave if he’s not allowed to perform, says Bakare The Federal High Court, Abuja, had on January 26, 2021, ordered the final forfeiture of funds belonging to Yari domiciled in Zenith and Polaris Banks. While $56, 056.75 was lodged in Polaris Bank, N12.9 million, N11.2m, $303m, N217, 388.04 and $311.8m were kept in different Zenith Bank accounts in the name of Yari and his companies. [ICYMI] Herdsmen crisis: What I told Sunday Igboho –Tunde Bakare The EFCC spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren confirmed that the ex- governor was grilled at the Lagos office of the commission, adding that he has been released to go home. READ ALSO: Ooni failed Yoruba by not telling Buhari truth about killer herdsmen —Sunday Igboho